      <h3>Worklights</h3>
      <p>The dual front LEDs (10) turn on with the switch and stay on for 20&nbsp;seconds after switch-off. They light the immediate work surface only &mdash; not a flashlight. If they flash, the battery may be low; if they still flash with a charged battery, have the tool evaluated at a service center.</p>

      <h2>Maintenance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cleaning:</strong> blow dust out of all air vents with clean, dry air at least weekly (wear eye protection). Use a dry cloth on the housing &mdash; never solvents, harsh chemicals, or liquids, which can weaken the plastic.</li>
        <li><strong>Plunge rods:</strong> wipe with a <em>dry</em> cloth only. They need no lubrication &mdash; lubricant attracts dust and reduces performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Waxing:</strong> for smooth motor-to-base movement, apply standard paste or liquid wax to the outside of the motor and inside of the base, let dry, and buff off.</li>
        <li>The charger and battery pack are not serviceable. For repairs, maintenance, or adjustment, use a DeWALT factory or authorized service center and identical replacement parts.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Locking Lever Adjustment</h2>
      <p>When clamped, the locking lever should hold the motor firmly in the base without requiring excessive force. If it won&rsquo;t clamp without excessive force, or the motor still moves after clamping:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the locking lever &mdash; (12) on the fixed base or (39) on the plunge base.</li>
        <li>Using a hex wrench, turn the locking lever adjustment screw (23) in small increments &mdash; clockwise tightens the lever, counterclockwise loosens it.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Likely cause / action</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Tool will not start</td><td>Switch in OFF; battery not seated or discharged; Electronic Protection System tripped &mdash; reseat or recharge a fully charged pack.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Tool shuts off under load</td><td>Overload/overheat protection engaged. Reduce depth of cut and/or feed rate; let the pack cool and recharge.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Bit slips or vibrates</td><td>Collet nut not tight; wrong shank size; dull or oversized bit. Retighten (use ratchet method), use a sharp 1/4&Prime; bit no larger than 1-3/8&Prime; diameter.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Motor moves in the base when clamped</td><td>Adjust the locking lever clamping force (screw 23) &mdash; see above.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Plunge action stiff or restricted</td><td>Bent/damaged plunge rods from wrench contact; wipe rods with a dry cloth, do not lubricate.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Worklights flashing</td><td>Low battery &mdash; recharge. If still flashing with a charged pack, take the tool to a service center.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Variable speed erratic or non-functioning</td><td>Stop using immediately; take to a DeWALT factory or authorized service center for repair.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

